orig=About the beginning of the month a small brig left here for Oporto, and was telegraphed as having arrived there on the 12th day after her departure from here - Even 21 days is considered a good passage generally. - at the end of the month a brig arrived here 90 days out from Sicily. - This will give some idea of the weather of late on the Atlantic mno|Local time: mean|QC flag: missing|Image File: StJohnsNFLDCas_USSI-401_M1958_1869-02-01_CP.jpg
